My husband chose this place for his birthday brunch celebration with our friends last Saturday. Waiter attending to us was nice and cheerful though he really only started taking our orders and drinks 15-20 mins after. That's not really an issue in a normal scenario except your table is restricted to only 90 mins, so a little something to plan your activity or celebration around with.  Most of us ordered Ropa Vieja and it was so tender and delicious. Everyone ordered various Sangrias but I did stick to Fresa/s which was vodka based, it was alright. I managed to drink a glass and a half of it, time went by pretty quick and before we knew it, we were being asked to pay (30 mins before the 90 mins was up) and leave.  We liked it there but we didn't enjoy the feeling of being rushed. Overall still a good spot, just keep the strict time element in mind.. :)

It was just an OK experience. I've been to Calle Ocho years ago when they had a different location, for brunch, and always wanted to go back for regular food. The brunch I had at the time was Shrimp and Grits. That seemed microwaved as it arrived to party of three lukewarm. I remember being served big cups of unlimited sangria for 90 min. The drinks sold me at that time.  Fast forward to now. Different location. Different vibe. I was a party of two celebrating a birthday that we made reservations for. We were not asked about it nor did we receive a complimentary Happy Birthday greeting. No worries. He ordered something that was not on the menu because it was the nightly special. It was a rabbit dish with mojo seasoning and a Cole slaw. The batter tasted like Adobo and lime. He said it was great! I ordered the Ceviche, Pulpo y Camarones. The Ceviche came garnished with cilantro and sat in a thick cilantro based soup. I had to send it back because that's all you could taste. I opted for The Chicarron which despite the menu description tasted like baby shrimp in a Sweet Thai Chilli sauce on top of coleslaw that had absorbed the flavor.  For our entree we decided to share Mar y Tierra which was braised short rib with 1/2 lb lobster. The plate arrived to the table with half a lobster shell and maybe 2oz of lobster meat. When brought to our waiters attention the manager was sent over. He was pleasant but basically told us that we should be rest assured because everything is weighed. He also stated that the weight is also similar to that of a lobster tail which perplexed me because a lobster tail is way bigger than what was served. They clearly took our meat off the shell, sliced it, cut it, and placed it back, hoping the customer wouldn't notice. Fast forward, the manager goes to talk to the kitchen. He brought us two claws and a cracker. That was kind of him.  The short rib had a lot of fat and connective tissue. And was a little hard to enjoy. We ordered another round of drinks hoping to make the most of the night. We had the mojioto sangria, Havana sangria, and fresas sangria. The Havana had coconut rum and banana liquor but tasted like orange rind, the fresas sangria had a thick syrup (cough syrup) taste to it. Overall, would I recommend it? Been here twice and had my fill so, No I would not recommend this place.

Calle Ocho was very nice. Located right off Central Park in a hotel. Went for brunch with the girls and the food was amazing. One set price for unlimited sangria (4 choices of white and 4 choices of red), and food. Multiple options. Had the Vaca Frita which is skirt steak, friend eggs, latin fried rice, and avocado. It was so good. The eggs were cooked over easy, steak had great flavor and the rice was really good, was typical rice and beans with a twist of asian fried rice. Had the Tropical White sangria which has a rum in it with flavors of pineapple, mango, and orange i believe was the last one. They had spanish music playing, a mix of salsa and reggaeton. They have a bar area as soon as you walk in with seating to the back. Restrooms. Accept cards and cash. For attire, I would do a classy clean look. My friend wore jeans but a dress blouse and dressy shoes. I had heels and a classy jumpsuit. Decor was very cute and appropriate. I would recommend going and checking it out.
